name: XV
bio__summary: Donavan LaMond Johnson (born July 9, 1985) better known by his stage name XV is an American rapper, singer and songwriter from Wichita, Kansas.

name: Rich Boy
bio__summary: Marece Benjamin Richards (born September 2, 1983), better known by his stage name Rich Boy, is an American rapper from Mobile, Alabama. He is best known for the hit single "Throw Some D's". His self-titled debut album was released in early 2007.

name: Dayton Family
bio__summary: The Dayton Family is an American hip hop group from Flint, Michigan. The group is composed of Ira "Bootleg" Dorsey, Raheen "Shoestring" Peterson and Matt "Backstabba" Hinkle.

name: Death Grips
bio__summary: Death Grips is an American experimental hip hop band from Sacramento, California, formed in 2010. The group consists of vocalist MC Ride, drummer/producer Zach Hill, and keyboardist/producer/recording engineer Andy Morin.

name: Lemdi & Moax
bio__summary: Lemdi & Moax are two MC from Val Maubuée. They are member of the Val Mobb Industries crew.

name: Bastos
bio__summary: Bastos is French rapper from Chelles (Seine et Marne).

name: O'Rosko Raricim
bio__summary: O'Rosko Raricim born in 1978 in Congo. Is a french rapper from Meaux (Seine et Marne). He was a member of the Ghetto Fabulous Gang.

name: Mystik
bio__summary: Mystik born Ghislain Loussingui Diabaka in 1978 at Pointe-Noire (Congo). Is a french rapper from Meaux (Seine et Marne). He was a member of the Bisso Na Bisso group.

name: Lil Kim
bio__summary: Kimberly Denise Jones (born July 11, 1974), known professionally as Lil' Kim, is an American rapper, singer born and raised in Brooklyn, New York.

name: Ciara
bio__summary: Ciara Princess Harris is an American singer, songwriter, dancer, and model. Born in Austin, Texas, she traveled around the world during her childhood, eventually moving to Atlanta, Georgia where she joined the girl group Hearsay.

name: Boulox
bio__summary: Dijibi Diop (Better known has Boulox) was a French rapper from Pont-de-Sèvre (Boulogne-Billancourt, Paris). He was one of the original member of the Mo'vez Lang group, with LIM, Cens Nino, Kaizer and Furax. He passed away in 2016 due to medical issues.

name: Tierra Whack
bio__summary: Tierra Helena Whack (born August 11, 1995) is an American rapper, singer, and songwriter. She originally performed as "Dizzle Dizz" as a teenager, but later on reverted to her birth name in 2017.

name: Bushwick Bill
bio__summary: Richard Stephen Shaw (December 8, 1966 – June 9, 2019) was a Jamaican-American rapper and record producer better known by his stage name Bushwick Bill. He was best known as a member of the pioneering Texas hip hop group Geto Boys, a group he originally joined as a dancer in 1986 as Little Billy.

name: Pharrell Williams
bio__summary: Pharrell Lanscilo Williams (born April 5, 1973) is an American rapper, singer, songwriter, record producer, entrepreneur, and fashion designer from Virginia Beach, Virginia. Williams and Chad Hugo comprise the record production duo The Neptunes, producing hip hop and R&B music.

name: David Banner
bio__summary: Lavell William Crump (born April 11, 1974), known professionally as David Banner, is an American rapper, record producer, actor, activist, and philanthropist from Jackson, Mississippi.\r\n\r\n

name: Soso Maness
bio__summary: Soso Maness is a french Rapper from Font Vert, Marseille.

name: Peezy
bio__summary: Peezy is an American Rapper from Detroit Michigan born on November 5, 1991. He is a member of the Team Eastside crew.

name: Tyga
bio__summary: Micheal Ray Stevenson (born November 19, 1989), known by his stage name Tyga (a backronym for Thank you God always), is an American rapper, songwriter, singer, actor and television personality from Gardena, California.

name: Md Beddah
bio__summary: Deyan Minchev better known by his stage name Md Beddah, is a Bulgarian  rapper and composer from Vratsa born in 1988. He is a member of the XPRSN crew.

name: Roxanne Shante
bio__summary: Roxanne Shante (born Lolita Shanté Gooden; November 9, 1969) is an American hip hop musician and rapper. Born and raised in the Queensbridge Projects of Queens, New York City, Shante first gained attention through the Roxanne Wars and was part of the Juice Crew.

name: Ms Tee
bio__summary: Trishell Williams better known by his stage name Ms Tee, is an american rapper from Treme, New Orleans. She was the first female signature of Cash Money.

name: Luniz
bio__summary: Luniz (formerly the LuniTunes) is a american duo from Oakland, California, formed by Yukmouth and Numskull. The group is best known for the internationally successful hit "I Got 5 on It".

name: Da Brat
bio__summary: Shawntae Harris (born April 14, 1974), better known by her stage name Da Brat, is an American rapper and actress from Chicago, Illinois.

name: Noname
bio__summary: Fatimah Nyeema Warner (born September 18, 1991), better known by her stage name Noname, is an American rapper, poet and record producer from  Bronzeville, Chicago,  Illinois.

name: Cellyru
bio__summary: Cellyru is an american rapper from Sacramento, California. He is a member of the Mozzy Records label.\r\n

name: Dangerous Crew
bio__summary: The Dangerous Crew was an American hip hop band formed by Oakland, California rapper and producer Todd "Too Short" Shaw. The Dangerous Crew consisted of both live musicians and rappers: Stuart "Shorty B" Jordan (bass, guitar, drums), Ramone "Pee-Wee" Gooden (keyboards, drums, guitar), Anthony "Ant" Banks (keyboards, drum programming, mixing), Sean G (live drums), and rappers Too Short, Mhisani "Goldy" Miller, FM Blue, Dangerous Dame, Russell "Rappin' Ron" Royster, Ant Diddley Dog, Robert "Spice 1" Green Jr. and Damani "Father Dom" Khaleel.

name: Seagram
bio__summary: Seagram Miller (April 13, 1970 – July 31, 1996) was an American rapper from Oakland, California. Miller was shot to death in a drive-by shooting on July 31, 1996.

name: Kilo G
bio__summary: Born Robert L. Johnson (August 28, 1976, 15th of January, 1997), Kilo G was an american rapper from New Orlean, Louisiana. He was a member of the early Cash Money record label. The 15th of January, 1997, Kilo-G was shot to death.

name: Lil Blood
bio__summary: Lil Blood, is an american rapper from West Oakland.

name: J Stallin
bio__summary: Jovan Smith (born January 25, 1983), better known by his stage name J. Stalin (also stylized as J Stalin or J-Stalin), is a rapper from the Cypress Village housing projects in West Oakland.

name: Chingy
bio__summary: Howard Bailey Jr. (Born March 9, 1980), better known by his stage name Chingy, is an American rapper and actor from St Louis, Missouri.

name: Lil Troy
bio__summary: Troy Lane Birklett (born February 24, 1966), better known by his stage name Lil' Troy, is an American rapper. He is the founder of the Short Stop label and was a member or the Mass 187 group.

name: M.O.P.
bio__summary: M.O.P. (short for Mash Out Posse) is an American hip hop duo from Brooklyn, New York City. Composed of rappers Billy Danze and Lil' Fame. Although they maintain a strong underground following, they are mainly known for the song "Ante Up", released on their Warriorz album in 2000.

name: Domo Genesis
bio__summary: Dominique Marquis Cole (born March 9, 1991), known professionally as Domo Genesis, is an American rapper and disc jockey (DJ) from Los Angeles, California. He is a member of Odd Future.

name: Biz Markie
bio__summary: Marcel Theo Hall (born April 8, 1964), better known by his stage name Biz Markie, is an American rapper, beatboxer, DJ, and a comedian from Long Island, New York.

name: Skee-Lo
bio__summary: Antoine Roundtree (born March 27, 1975), better known by his stage name Skee-Lo, is an American rapper. He is best known for his 1995 song, "I Wish".

name: Lost Boyz
bio__summary: Lost Boyz is a hip hop group from South Jamaica, Queens, New York City formed by MC Mr. Cheeks, backup MC and promoter Freaky Tah, DJ Spigg Nice (Ronald Blackwell) and Pretty Lou (Eric Ruth).

name: Crime Mob
bio__summary: Crime Mob is an American hip hop group from Atlanta consisting of seven members: M.I.G., Cyco Black, Princess, Lil' Jay, Diamond, and Killa C. The group is best known for their songs "Knuck If You Buck" and "Rock Yo Hips".

name: Krilino
bio__summary: Krilino is a french rapper from Lille.

name: Young Scooter
bio__summary: Kenneth Edward Bailey (born March 28, 1986), better known by his stage name Young Scooter, is an American rapper from Atlanta, Georgia. He is affiliated with Freebandz and 1017 Brick Squad Records.

name: Lil Reese
bio__summary: Tavares Taylor (born January 6, 1993), known by his stage name Lil Reese, is an American rapper from Chicago, Illinois. As of 2012, Lil Reese was signed to Def Jam Recordings.

name: Ärsenik
bio__summary: Ärsenik is a rap group based in Villiers-le-Bel, France, founded in 1992, and made up of two brothers, Lino (Gaëlino M'Bani) and Calbo (Calboni M'Bani), whose family is originally from Congo.

name: DJ Spanish Fly
bio__summary: DJ Spanish is an American DJ from Memphis, Tennessee. He is regularly considered as one of the father of the Memphis rap sound.

name: Trippie Redd
bio__summary: Michael Lamar White IV (born June 18, 1999), known professionally as Trippie Redd, is an American rapper and singer from Canton, Ohio.

name: Sara Hebe
bio__summary: Sara Hebe (Born 9 july 1983) is a rapper and hip-hop artist from Buenos Aires, Argentina.

name: Violadores del Verso
bio__summary: Violadores del Verso (Spanish for: Lyrical Molesters or Verse Rapists), also known as Doble V, are a rap music crew from Zaragoza, Spain.\r\nThe group is composed by Kase.O, Sho Hai, Lírico and R de Rumba.

name: Baneva
bio__summary: Baneva is a Turkish rapper from Ankara.

name: Ezhel
bio__summary: Ezhel (real name Ömer Sercan İpekçioğlu) is a Turkish rapper from Ankara whose music blends trap, hip-hop and reggae.

name: Joey Le Soldat
bio__summary: Joel Windtoin Sawadogo known as Joey Le Soldat, is a rapper from Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso.

name: Koba la D
bio__summary: Koba la D is a french rapper from Evry, Essonne.

name: Payroll Giovanni
bio__summary: Payroll Giovanni is an american rapper from Detroit, Michigan born in 1988. He was signed to Young Jeezy’s CTE alongside his groupmates Doughboyz Cashout but is now independent and releases material as an individual artist.

name: DJ Fresh
bio__summary: Marqus Brown, known as DJ Fresh (born in Baltimore, Maryland) is an American hip hop producer based in Oakland, California. Best known for is Tonite Show series of albums.

name: G Perico
bio__summary: G Perico (born Jeremy Nash) is an american rapper from South Central, Los Angeles, California.

name: Maes
bio__summary: Maes is a French rapper from Sevran, Seine-Saint-Denis.

name: Fabe
bio__summary: Fabrice "Fabe" (born in 1971 Paris, France) is a French rapper from 10th District of Paris. He is one of the founders of Scred Connexion.

name: Benash
bio__summary: Benash is a French rapper from Boulogne-Billancourt, Hauts-de-Seine. He is a member of the 40000 Gang group.

name: Conway
bio__summary: Demond Price  known professionally as Conway is an American rapper from Buffalo. He is the founder of Griselda Records alongside is brother Westside Gunn.

name: Maxo Kream
bio__summary: Emekwanem Ogugua Biosah Jr. (born March 29, 1990), better known by his stage name Maxo Kream, is an American rapper and record producer from Alief, Houston, Texas.

name: Dilated peoples
bio__summary: Dilated Peoples is an American hip hop group from Los Angeles, California. The group is formed by Dj Babu, Evidence and Rakaa.

name: Hopsin
bio__summary: Marcus Jamal Hopson (born July 18, 1985), better known by his stage name Hopsin, is an American rapper, record producer, director and actor from Panorama City, Los Angeles, California.

name: Kamaiyah
bio__summary: Kamaiyah Jamesha Johnson (born March 13, 1992) is an American rapper and singer from Sacramento, California.

name: Mob Figaz
bio__summary: Mob Figaz is a Bay Area hip hop group formed by C-Bo in 1997. The members consist of Husalah, Rydah J. Klyde, and The Jacka from Pittsburg, Fed-X from Richmond and AP.9 from Oakland, California.

name: Husalah
bio__summary: James "Husalah" Ratliff (born May 13, 1979), is an american rapper from Pittsburg, California. He began his career with the Pittsburg group the Mob Figaz, whose first album, C-Bo's Mob Figaz, was released in 1999.

name: C-Bo
bio__summary: Shawn Thomas (born January 14, 1972), better known by his stage name C-Bo, is an American rapper from Sacramento, California.

name: N.O.R.E.
bio__summary: Victor Santiago, Jr. (born September 6, 1977), best known by his stage name N.O.R.E., formerly Noreaga, is an American rapper. Santiago first rose to prominence as one half of the East Coast hip hop duo Capone-N-Noreaga (C-N-N), alongside fellow Queens-based rapper Capone.

name: Cardi B
bio__summary: Belcalis Almanzar (born October 11, 1992), known professionally as Cardi B, is an American rapper. Born and raised in Highbridge, South Bronx, New York City.

name: 6ix9ine
bio__summary: Daniel Hernandez (born May 8, 1996), known by his stage name 6ix9ine ("six-nine"), also known as Tekashi69 or simply Tekashi, is an American rapper from Bushwick, Brooklyn.

name: Blueprint Hakeem
bio__summary: Blueprint Hakeem is a Cameroonian rapper, from the Bafut tribe in the North West Region of Cameroon.

name: Drakeo The Ruler
bio__summary: Drakeo the Ruler is a american rapper from South Central, Los Angles, California.

name: L'Skadrille
bio__summary: L'Skadrille is a French rap band from Saint-Cyr-l'École, Yvelines. Formed in 1996 by 13or (Trésor) et 16ar (César).

name: 03 Greedo
bio__summary: 03 Greedo is an American rapper/singer from Watts, Los Angeles, California.

name: 21 Savage
bio__summary: Shayaa Bin Abraham-Joseph (born October 22, 1992), better known by his stage name 21 Savage, is an American rapper from Atlanta of Dominican and Haitian descent.

name: Lil pump
bio__summary: Gazzy Garcia (born August 17, 2000), known professionally as Lil Pump, is an American rapper, producer from Miami, Florida.

name: Ministère A.M.E.R
bio__summary: The Ministère AMER (Action, Musique Et Rap) is a French hip hop group from Sarcelles, consisting of the rappers Passi and Stomy Bugsy, DJ Ghetch, and the producer/manager Kenzy.

name: Xavier Wulf
bio__summary: Xavier (once known as Ethelwulf) Wulf is an American rapper from East Memphis, Tennessee. Wulf was a member of the rap outfit Raider Klan.

name: Laioung
bio__summary: Laïoung (born Giuseppe Bockarie Consoli, 13/08/1992), is a rapper and Italian producer. He is the cofounder of the rap crew RRR Mob.

name: Griby
bio__summary: Griby is a Ukrainian rap group from Kiev, Ukraine.

name: AKA
bio__summary: Kiernan Jarryd Forbes, known by his stage name AKA, is a South African hip hop recording artist and record producer.

name: Nasty C
bio__summary: Nsikayesizwe David Junior Ngcobo (born 11 February 1997), better known by his stage name Nasty C, is a South African rapper, songwriter and record producer from Durban.

name: Cassper Nyovest
bio__summary: Refiloe Maele Phoolo (born 16 December 1990), professionally known as Cassper Nyovest, is a South African rapper from Mahikeng. His debut album Tsholofelo was released on 18 July 2014. He is currently signed to his own independent label and media company, Family Tree.

name: Moha La Squale
bio__summary: Mohamed Bellahmed, better know as Moha La Squale (born 24 February 1995) , is a French rapper from the 20th district of Paris.

name: Young MC
bio__summary: Marvin Young (born May 10, 1967), better known by his stage name Young M.C., is an English-born American singer, rapper and actor from the Queens, New York. He is best known for his 1989 hit "Bust a Move".

name: Kevin Abstract
bio__summary: Kevin Abstract (born Ian Simpson; July 16, 1996), is an American rapper, singer-songwriter, and director. Abstract is a founding member of the Brockhampton band.

name: Loud
bio__summary: Loud is the stage name of Simon Cliche Trudeau, a Canadian rapper from Montreal. Formerly associated with the band Loud Lary Ajust, he released his debut solo recording Une année record in 2017.

name: Woodie Smalls
bio__summary: Woodie Smalls (born 18 June 1996) is a Belgian rapper born and raised in Sint-Niklaas, Belgium.

name: STR
bio__summary: STR is a Belgian rapper from Bruxelles. He is a member of the 6 O'Clock Gang.

name: Phasm
bio__summary: Phasm is a Belgian rapper and beatmaker from Bruxelles. He is a member of the Six o'clock Gang. \r\n

name: Tela
bio__summary: Winston Rogers III, professionally known by his stage name Tela, is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee. He was associated with Eightball & MJG early in his career.

name: Frayser Boy
bio__summary: Frayser Boy (born February 21, 1979) is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee. At the 78th Academy Awards, he won the Academy Award for Best Original Song for "It's Hard out Here for a Pimp" along with Three 6 Mafia members Juicy J, Crunchy Black, and DJ Paul.

name: OG Boo Dirty
bio__summary: Lance Taylor, known as OG Boo Dirty, is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee.

name: Young Dolph
bio__summary: Adolph Thornton, Jr. (born August 11, 1985), better known by his stage name Young Dolph, is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee.\r\n\r\n

name: Lil Wyte
bio__summary: Patrick Lanshaw (born October 6, 1982), better known by his stage name Lil Wyte, is an American rapper from Frayser, Memphis, Tennessee. He is a member of the rap collective Hypnotize Minds and owner of the independent label Wyte Music.

name: Al Kapone
bio__summary: Alphonzo Bailey, better known by his stage name Al Kapone, is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee. Al Kapone is known principally for his underground success in the Memphis hip hop scene in the 1990s.

name: Project Pat
bio__summary: Patrick Houston (born February 8, 1973), better known as Project Pat is an American rapper and actor originating from Memphis, Tennessee. He is the older brother of Juicy J, the co-founder of Three 6 Mafia.

name: La Chat
bio__summary: La Chat (born March 21, 1978) is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee. She is best known for her period as an artist on the Hypnotize Minds roster, and made regular guest appearances on many releases by other associated acts such as Three 6 Mafia and Gangsta Boo.

name: Tommy Wright III
bio__summary: Tommy Wright III (born May 6, 1976) is a underground gangsta rapper from Memphis, Tennessee that began his career during the early 90s. He is also the head of many Memphis rap groups including the Manson Family and Ten Wanted Men.

name: Indo G
bio__summary: Indo G (born Tobian Tools in 1973) is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee. First hitting the Memphis rap scene with fellow Memphian, Lil' Blunt, in the mid-1990s. He was also affiliated with the Three 6 Mafia.

name: Crunchy Black
bio__summary: Darnell Carlton (born August 20, 1974), better known by his stage name Crunchy Black, is an American rapper and Hype man. He was a member of the Three 6 Mafia until 2006.

name: Gangsta Blac
bio__summary: Gangsta Blac, (born 11 November 1974) is a American rapper from Memphis Tennessee. His career began as a member of the Three 6 Mafia DJ Paul in Memphis before going solo in the mid 1990s.

name: Gangsta Pat
bio__summary: Patrick Hall (born November 17, 1973), better known by his stage name Gangsta Pat, is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee who established himself in the Memphis underground during the late 1980s and is the son of Stax Records drummer, Willie Hall.

name: D' de Kabal
bio__summary: D' de Kabal (born 1974) is a french rapper, slamer, writer and director from Bobigny, Seine-Saint-Denis. He is one of the founder of the french rap group Kabal.

name: Roffe Ruff
bio__summary: Roffe Ruff is a Swedish hip hop and ragga artist and music producer from Gothenburg. His real identity remains a secret, and he always wears a skull mask in his appearances.

name: Roc Marciano
bio__summary: Rakeem Calief Myer (born February 11, 1978), better known by his stage name Roc Marciano, is an American rapper, and producer.\r\n\r\n

name: Starlito
bio__summary: Jermaine Eric Shute (born December 15, 1984), better known by his stage name Starlito (formerly All $tar Cashville Prince) is an American rapper from Nashville, Tennessee.

name: Peja
bio__summary: Ryszard "Peja" Andrzejewski is a Polish rap musician, songwriter and producer. He is best known as the frontman of the Polish rap group Slums Attack.

name: Nusky & Vaati
bio__summary: Nusky and Vaati is a french rap duo, composed of Vaati (producer) and Nusky (rapper).

name: Hyacinthe
bio__summary: Hyacinthe is a French rapper from crew DFHDGB (which stands for "Des Faux Hipster et Des Grosses Bites" and means "False Hipsters and Big Dicks") composed of rapper LOAS and beatmaker Krampf. His first album "Sarah" is out on September 29, 2017.

name: Fler
bio__summary: Patrick Losensky (born 3 April 1982), known professionally as Fler is a German rapper from West Berlin.

name: Bushido
bio__summary: Anis Mohamed Youssef Ferchichi (born 28 September 1978), better known as Bushido, is a German rapper. In 2004, he and fellow rapper D-Bo founded the record label ersguterjunge.

name: Big Hawk
bio__summary: John Edward Hawkins (November 15, 1969 – May 1, 2006), better known as H.A.W.K. or Big Hawk was an American rapper from Houston, Texas and a founding member of the late DJ Screw's rap group the Screwed Up Click.

name: KLC
bio__summary: Craig Stephen Lawson a.k.a. KLC also know as the Drum major, (born July 15, 1969) is an American record producer from the Third Ward of New Orleans, Louisiana. He found fame as a member of No Limit Records' in-house production team, Beats by the Pound.

name: Paul Wall
bio__summary: Paul Michael Slayton (born March 11, 1981), better known by his stage name Paul Wall, is an American rapper from Houston, Texas. He is affiliated with Swishahouse Records.

name: Mike Jones
bio__summary: Michael Jones (born November 18, 1981) is an American rapper, actor, and entrepreneur. He initially was with Swishahouse, then left to found his own label, Ice Age.

name: Trae Tha Truth
bio__summary: Frazier Othel Thompson III (born July 3, 1980), better known by his stage name Trae tha Truth or simply Trae, is an American hip hop recording artist from Houston, Texas.

name: Fat Pat
bio__summary: Patrick Lamark Hawkins (December 4, 1970 – February 3, 1998), better known by his stage name Fat Pat was an American rapper from Houston, Texas.

name: Big Moe
bio__summary: Kenneth Doniell Moore (August 20, 1974 – October 14, 2007), better known by his stage name Big Moe, was an American rapper from Houston, Texas.

name: Lil' Keke
bio__summary: Marcus Lakee Edwards (born March 29, 1976), better known by his stage name Lil' Keke, is an American rapper from Houston, Texas and original member of the Southern hip hop collective Screwed Up Click.

name: Lil' Flip
bio__summary: Wesley Eric Weston, Jr.[1][2] (born March 3, 1981), better known by his stage name Lil' Flip, is an American rapper from Cloverland, Houston, Texas.

name: Michael "5000" Watts
bio__summary: Michael "5000" Watts is a record producder from Houston, Texas. He is one of the founder of Swishahouse Record.

name: Higher Brothers
bio__summary: Higher Brothers are a four-man rap group from China. The members of the group are 马思唯 (MaSiWei), 丁震 (DZ), 杨俊逸 (Psy.P), and 谢宇杰 (Melo).

name: New African Poets
bio__summary: New African Poets (NAP) are a French hip hop group from Strasbourg. The members of the group are Mustapha, Bilal, Malik, Aïssa, Mohammed and Karim. Most of the group come from the Neuhof quartier of Strasbourg.

name: Craig Mack
bio__summary: Craig Mack (May 10, 1970 – March 12, 2018) is an American rapper, who gained fame on Puff Daddy's Bad Boy Entertainment record label in the 1990s. Although his first single was released under the name MC EZ in 1988, he is best known for his 1994 hit single "Flava In Ya Ear", which was released under his real name.

name: Dead Prez
bio__summary: Dead Prez, is a hip hop duo from the United States, composed of stic.man and M-1, formed in 1996 in New York City. They are known for their confrontational style, combined with socialist lyrics focused on both militant social justice, Marxism, and Pan-Africanism. The duo maintains an ethical stance against corporate control over the media, especially hip hop record labels.

name: Yoon Mi Rae
bio__summary: Natasha Shanta Reid (born May 31, 1981), better known by her Korean name Yoon Mi-rae, is an American-born South Korean rapper and singer. She is currently a member of Korean hip hop trio MFBTY.

name: San E
bio__summary: Jung San (Korean: 정산; born January 23, 1985), more commonly known by his stage name San E (Korean: 산이), is a South Korean rapper.

name: Zico
bio__summary: Woo Ji-ho (Korean: 우지호; born September 14, 1992), widely known by his stage name, Zico (Korean: 지코), is a South Korean rapper, producer, singer-songwriter and leader of the boy group Block B, signed under the label Seven Seasons.

name: Enima
bio__summary: Samir Slimani, better known by is stage name Enima is a Canadian rapper from Montreal.

name: Kalash l'Afro
bio__summary: Kalash l'Afro (born in Berre-l'Étang, Bouches-du-Rhône in 1979) is a French rapper of Tunisian origin.

name: Infinit
bio__summary: Infinit’ is a rapper from Nice. He gained some notoriety with a song about Christian Estrosi which valued him prosecution.

name: VÎRUS
bio__summary: VÎRUS is a french rapper from Rouen, he is a member of the Asocial Club crew.

name: Saian Supa Crew
bio__summary: Saïan Supa Crew was a French hip hop collective that was composed of three groups: Explicit Samouraï, OFX and Simple Spirit. It formed in 1997 and separated in 2007 after the departure of one of its leaders (along with Feniksi), Leeroy Kesiah.

name: Gérard Baste
bio__summary: Matthieu Balanca, known as Gérard Baste, born on January 9, 1973, is a French rapper from Paris. He is a member of the Svinkels rap group.

name: 7ARI
bio__summary: Soufiane elhari is a rapper singer from Rabat (CYM). He was a member of Tawra crew.\r\n

name: Pacewon
bio__summary: Pacewon (born Jerome Derek Hinds, Jr.) is an American rapper and producer from Newark, New Jersey. He was a member of the Outsidaz group.

name: Jimmy Wopo
bio__summary: Travon DaShawn Frank Smart (January 13, 1997 – June 18, 2018), better known by his stage name Jimmy Wopo, was an American rapper from Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.

name: Key!
bio__summary: Key is an american from Atlanta, Georgia. He is a member of the Two-9 collective.

name: Nyzzy Nyce
bio__summary: DeAngelo Samuel, (born January 4, 1988) better known by his stage name Nyzzy Nyce (aka Nyzzy), is an American rapper from Fort Wayne, Indiana.

name: Gué Pequeno
bio__summary: Cosimo Fini better know as Gué Pequeno, is an Italian rapper from Milan.

name: Kaytranada
bio__summary: Louis Kevin Celestin (born August 25, 1992), known by his stage name Kaytranada, is a Haitian-Canadian DJ and record producer.

name: Watsky
bio__summary: George Virden Watsky (born September 15, 1986), known professionally as Watsky, is an American hip hop artist, author, and poet from San Francisco, California.

name: Enzo Dong
bio__summary: Enzo Dong (born 01/05/1991) is a Italian rapper from Don Guanella, Naples.

name: Allan Kingdom
bio__summary: Allan Kyariga (born January 6, 1994, better known by his stage name Allan Kingdom, is a Canadian rapper and record producer based in Saint Paul, Minnesota. He is a member of Thestand4rd along with Spooky Black, Bobby Raps, and Psymun.

name: D T F
bio__summary: DTF is a French band from Ivry-sur-Seine (94) composed by RTI and RKM. DTF stand for “Dans Ta Face” (In your face).

name: EarthGang
bio__summary: EarthGang are an American rap duo composed of rappers Johnny "Olu O. Fann" Venus and Doctur "Eian Undrai Parker" Dot. Formed in 2008 in Atlanta, Georgia, EarthGang released its first EP, The Better Party.

name: Gkr
bio__summary: GKR Is a rapper from Reykjavik, Iceland.

name: Ksir Makoza
bio__summary: Ksir Makoza is a French rapper from Marseille. He was a member of the group 1K2Plus.

name: Pee Froiss

name: Madlib

name: Skinny Pimp

The original four members of the group are Imani, Slimkid3, Bootie Brown, and Fatlip. DJ Mark Luv was the group's first DJ, followed by producer J-Swift and then J Dilla.

name: Slim Thug

name: Young Buck

name: Tech N9ne
